	        <p>40 years ago, before the internet and cell phones, we all could manage all of our contacts easily in a simple address book.  Most of us had an average of 25 people in their address books.  Most sales people had an average of 100 people in their address books.  It was relatively easy to keep track of and keep up with all of our contacts.</p>
